  "response": "## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Podcast Player Without Transcripts  \n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Auditory Access, Screen Reader Semantic  \n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion, Keyboard & Motor, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 2 |\n| MINOR | 0 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed  \nNone (both escalated perspectives have findings)\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**  \n- [Missing transcript for audio content] \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.2.1  \n- [New episode badge lacks text alternative] \u2014 Screen Reader Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.1.1  \n- [Speed change not announced to screen readers] \u2014 Screen Reader Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.3  \n\n**Content Author**  \n- [Missing transcript for audio content] \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.2.1  \n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification  \n- Transcript completeness for all episodes  \n- Audio description coverage for visual-only information in episode intros  \n\n### Recommended Next Step  \n**BLOCK** \u2014 CRITICAL findings present (missing transcripts) prevent access for deaf/hard-of-hearing users.\n\n---\n\n## Full Finding Details\n\n```\n**Finding:** Audio content has no transcript or link to transcript as required by WCAG 1.2.1  \n**WCAG:** 1.2.1 Audio Only  \n**Perspective:** Auditory Access  \n**Severity:** CRITICAL  \n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)  \n**Evidence:** `<audio>` element exists but no `<track kind=\"transcript\">` or adjacent transcript markup  \n**Fix:** Add visible transcript section below player or implement `<track kind=\"transcript\">` with valid `src`  \n**Finding ID:** podcast-player-missing-transcript  \n**Fingerprint:** 3a7d4f2e  \n**Source:** a11y-critic  \n**Trend:** new  \n**Perspective alarms:** auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\n```\n\n```\n**Finding:** \"New episode\" badge uses only a red dot with `role=\"img\"` \u2014 no text alternative  \n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-Text Content  \n**Perspective:** Screen Reader Semantic  \n**Severity:** MAJOR  \n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)  \n**Evidence:** `<span class=\"new-badge\" role=\"img\" />` with no `aria-label` or visible text  \n**Fix:** Add `aria-label=\"New\"` to the badge and consider adding visible text like \"(New)\"  \n**Finding ID:** new-badge-missing-text  \n**Fingerprint:** 8b6c2d91  \n**Source:** a11y-critic  \n**Trend:** new  \n**Perspective alarms:** auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\n```\n\n```\n**Finding:** Speed control changes not announced to screen readers via `aria-live`  \n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages  \n**Perspective:** Screen Reader Semantic  \n**Severity:** MAJOR  \n**Route to:** Front-End Dev  \n**Evidence:** `<select>` updates playback rate but no `aria-live` region announces the change  \n**Fix:** Add `aria-live=\"polite\"` region that announces \"Playback speed set to [X]x\" on change  \n**Finding ID:** speed-control-missing-announcement  \n**Fingerprint:** 5f1a9d3c  \n**Source:** a11y-critic  \n**Trend:** new  \n**Perspective alarms:** auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\n```\n\n---\n\n## Code-Level Evidence\n\n1. **Missing transcript**  \n   ```jsx\n   <audio ref={audioRef} src={currentEpisode ? `/audio/${currentEpisode.id}.mp3` : undefined} />\n   ```\n   No `<track kind=\"transcript\">` element present for any audio\n\n2. **New episode badge**  \n   ```jsx\n   {ep.isNew && <span className=\"new-badge\" role=\"img\" />}\n   ```\n   No `aria-label` or visible text to indicate \"new\" status\n\n3. **Speed control**  \n   ```jsx\n   <select id=\"speed-select\" value={speed} onChange={handleSpeedChange} aria-label=\"Playback speed\">\n     <option value={0.75}>0.75x</option>\n     <option value={1}>1x</option>\n     <option value={1.25}>1.25x</option>\n     <option value={1.5}>1.5x</option>\n     <option value={2}>2x</option>\n   </select>\n   ```\n   No `aria-live` region to announce speed changes\n\n---\n\n## Additional Recommendations\n\n1. **Add transcript section**  \n   ```jsx\n   {currentEpisode && (\n     <div className=\"transcript-section\" aria-live=\"polite\">\n       <h2>Transcript</h2>\n       <p>Transcript for {currentEpisode.title}...</p>\n     </div>\n   )}\n   ```\n\n2. **Improve new episode indicator**  \n   ```jsx\n   {ep.isNew && (\n     <span className=\"new-badge\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"New\">\n       New\n     </span>\n   )}\n   ```\n\n3. **Add speed announcement**  \n   ```jsx\n   const [speedAnnouncement, setSpeedAnnouncement] = useState('');\n   \n   useEffect(() => {\n     if (speedAnnouncement) {\n       setTimeout(() => setSpeedAnnouncement(''), 5000);\n     }\n   }, [speedAnnouncement]);\n   \n   // Add this to player bar\n   <div aria-live=\"polite\" className=\"sr-only\">{speedAnnouncement}</div>\n   ```\n\n4. **Ensure episode change announcements**  \n   Add `aria-live` region that announces \"Now playing: [episode title]\" when currentEpisode changes",
